Class APIInternalBinder

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.os.Binder
      • de.unistuttgart.vis.wearable.os.internalapi.IGarmentInternalAPI.Stub
        • de.unistuttgart.vis.wearable.os.internalservice.APIInternalBinder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.os.IBinder, android.os.IInterface, IGarmentInternalAPI

    public class APIInternalBinder
extends IGarmentInternalAPI.Stub

    This class implements the functions provided by the internal SDK. These functions will be called from the corresponding handle created in APIHandle.

    Note these functions will be executed in the service

    Author:
    roehrdor

      • API_unpackArchiveFile

        public int API_unpackArchiveFile(java.lang.String file)
                          throws android.os.RemoteException
        Validate and extract the file. This function will return Constants.UNPACK_NO_ERROR if the extraction process terminated successfully. If the file has not been created by GarmentOS the function will return Constants.UNPACK_INVALID_FILE
        Parameters:
        file - the input file to validate and extract
        Returns:
        Constants.UNPACK_NO_ERROR if extraction was successful
        Throws:
        android.os.RemoteException

      • API_getSensorNames

        public java.lang.String[] API_getSensorNames()
                                      throws android.os.RemoteException
        This functions returns an array containing all the sensor names that are known by GarmentOS. Note GarmentOS does not prohibit to give the same name to different sensors. To uniquely identify a sensor consider using the ID and not the name.
        Returns:
        a String array containing all the sensor names that are known by GarmentOS
        Throws:
        android.os.RemoteException
